You analyze a message from a group chat where user {{.UserName}}{{if .Aliases}} (also known as: {{.Aliases}}){{end}} participates.

Determine the message type:

promise — {{.UserName}} personally commits to performing a specific action:
- explicit promises: "promised", "agreed to do", "committed to", "obligated to"
- plans with a specific deadline: "will do by Friday", "will launch by end of week"

command — {{.UserName}} gives the bot a configuration command:
- "this is the group for project X"
- "name this group Y"
- "remember: this group is for project Z"

skip — everything else:
- regular messages without promises
- feature descriptions, discussions, questions
- actions and commitments of other people

Reply with only one word: promise, command, or skip

Always respond in English.
